#
# WHAT IT IS
#   ampm is "application management + performance monitoring" — Stimulant's
#   Node.js supervisor / orchestration daemon for museum / lobby / trade-
#   show exhibit applications.  ampm reads a JSON `ampm.json` config that
#   describes which child app to launch (an Electron / Unity / native
#   binary), how to monitor it, what telemetry to emit (analytics events,
#   error reports, log rotation), and which remote-control surfaces to
#   expose:  console TCP, web dashboard, MQTT bus, and Open Sound Control
#   over UDP — the OSC surface lets exhibit operators trigger app actions
#   (next slide / restart / volume change) from a touchscreen OSC remote
#   (TouchOSC / QLab / etc.) on the same LAN.  ampm restarts itself when
#   `ampm-restart.json` changes (via `nodemon --watch`) and resurrects the
#   supervised app on crash.
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from start.js process.argv parsing)
#   ampm [CONFIG_FILES] [MODE] [NODEMON_OPTS...]
#
#   Positional arguments (Node.js stdlib `process.argv` indexing):
#     CONFIG_FILES    Comma-separated list of JSON configs; only the first
#                     file is used to locate the working dir, but all are
#                     forwarded to the server         [default: "ampm.json"]
#     MODE            Configuration mode key inside the JSON, selecting
#                     environment-specific overrides  [default: "default"]
#     NODEMON_OPTS    Any additional argv tokens are forwarded verbatim to
#                     the `nodemon` process supervising `server.js`
#                     (e.g. `--inspect`, `--no-colors`)
#
#   Behavior:
#     - Spawns `nodemon --verbose --exitcrash --watch <config> --watch
#       ampm-restart.json --ignore logs --ignore ampm-state.json
#       server.js <CONFIG_FILES> <MODE>`
#     - Touches `ampm-restart.json` / `ampm-state.json` in the config's
#       directory if absent
#     - On Windows, locates `nodemon` and `ampm`'s `server.js` via
#       `where nodemon` / `where ampm` to handle space-in-path quirks
#
# AXIS / CORPUS POSITION
#   Direct dependency on `node-osc` declared in package.json
#   `"dependencies"` — Myles Borins's canonical Node.js OSC library
#   (MylesBorins/node-osc, 460 stars).  node-osc implements OSC 1.0
#   server/client over UDP, ampm's `server.js` listens on a configurable
#   UDP port and routes `/ampm/...` OSC addresses to internal handlers
#   for the supervised exhibit application.  Verified via:
#     gh api repos/stimulant/ampm/contents/package.json
#       → "node-osc" in "dependencies"
#   This entry is the TS-Node=119 leader bump that CLOSES Axis 64
#   (OSC / Open Sound Control Library) at 1/1/1 three-language symmetry:
#     Rust   = rosc                       (R845, `sonic-pi-tool`, lpil)
#     Go     = hypebeast/go-osc           (R846, `broscoli`,       holoplot)
#     TS-Node = node-osc (MylesBorins)    (R847, `ampm`,           stimulant)
#   Reaches the triple-119 landmark Rust=Go=TS-Node=119.
#
#   No completion for `ampm` ships with Apple zsh
#   (/usr/share/zsh/*/functions) or Homebrew zsh-completions
#   (/opt/homebrew/share/zsh/site-functions) — confirmed absent.
# ============================================================================

_ampm() {
    _arguments \
        '1:config files (comma-separated, default ampm.json):_files -g "*.json"' \
        '2:mode (default "default"):' \
        '*:nodemon option:'
}

_ampm "$@"
